UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 181/GA
1 AN ACT relating to schools and declaring an emergency.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 160.145 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) As used in this section:
5 (a) "Family member" means:
6 1. A parent, brother, sister, son, daughter, aunt, uncle, cousin, or
7 grandparent related to the student by consanguinity, affinity, or
8 adoption; or
9 2. An adult that resides in the same household as the student;
10 (b) "Parent" means a parent, legal guardian, a person acting as a parent in the
11 absence of a parent or guardian, or other individual[person] or agency
12 responsible for the[a] student;
13 (c) "Private electronic communication" means electronic communication that
14 involves direct one-on-one or group conversations that are only accessible
15 to the participants;
16 (d) "Qualified school volunteer" means an adult who:
17 1. Is not:
18 a. A school district employee; or
19 b. Enrolled in the school district; and
20 2. Has served the school or school district at any point during the current
21 school year:
22 a. As a student teacher, a nonfaculty coach or assistant coach, a
23 nonfaculty sponsor of an extracurricular program or activity, or
24 a school-sponsored academic tutor; or
25 b. In a nonfaculty student services role designated as a qualified
26 school volunteer by the local board of education.
27 (e) "School district employee[ or volunteer]":
