1 1. Means a school administrator, classified or contract employee who is
2 not enrolled in the school district,[or] certified employee[ of a school
3 district, school volunteer], or compensated nonfaculty coach or assistant
4 coach; and
5 2. Includes any Kentucky Department of Education or educational
6 cooperative employee who is assigned to a school or area technology
7 center within the school district[, student teacher, or sponsor of an
8 extracurricular program or activity];
9 (f)[ (d)] "Traceable communication system" means one (1) or more electronic
10 school notification and communication programs or applications that:
11 1. Are designated by a local board of education in accordance with
12 subsection (2) of this section;
13 2. Trace all communications sent to or by a student; and
14 3. Provide parents an opportunity to access and review those
15 communications; and
16 (g)[(e)] "Unauthorized electronic communication":
17 1. Means private[an] electronic communication with a student enrolled in
18 a school district by the[a] school district's[district] employee or
19 qualified school volunteer who is not the student's family member that
20 occurs outside of a designated traceable communication system and
21 without prior written parental consent;[ and]
22 2. Includes any private electronic communication with a student or
23 students enrolled in the school district through a personal email
24 account, text messaging, social media, or other private electronic
25 [notification and ]communication program[programs] outside of the
26 traceable communication system[.]; and
27 3. Does not include:
Page 2 of 8
SB018110.100 - 175 - XXXX 1/27/2026 4:38 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 181/GA
1 a. Virtual school instruction;
2 b. Electronic translation services;
3 c. Electronic communication with any telephone number provided
4 by a parent for the purpose of school communication with that
5 parent;
6 d. Electronic communication in which a parent of the student is
7 included as a recipient or participant;
8 e. Voice communication on an official telephone number affiliated
9 with the school or school district;
10 f. Social media posts and comments that are not private electronic
11 communication;
12 g. Electronic communication related to commercial products or
13 services with a telephone number, email address, or other
14 electronic account affiliated with a lawful commercial business;
15 h. Secure messaging for healthcare providers; or
16 i. Electronic communication between a school resource officer or
17 director of pupil personnel and a student in which the principal,
18 vice principal, or a school-based mental health services provider,
19 as defined by KRS 158.4416, is included as a recipient or
20 participant.
21 (2) Each local board of education shall designate a traceable communication system[ to
22 be the exclusive means] for [a ]school district employees and qualified school
23 volunteers[employee or volunteer] to communicate electronically with students
24 enrolled in the school district. The principal of each public school shall provide
25 parents written or electronic notification within the first ten (10) days of the school
26 year of each electronic school notification and communication program designated
27 within the traceable communication system. The notification shall include
Page 3 of 8
SB018110.100 - 175 - XXXX 1/27/2026 4:38 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 181/GA
1 instructions for parents to access and review communications sent through each
2 electronic school notification and communication program.
3 (3) (a) [Except as provided in subsections (4) and (5) of this section, ]A school
4 district employee or qualified school volunteer shall not engage in
5 unauthorized electronic communication[communicate electronically with a
6 student:
7 1. Outside of the traceable communication system designated by the local
8 board of education; or
9 2. Through an unauthorized electronic communication program or
10 application].
11 (b) A school district employee that violates paragraph (a) of this subsection
12 may[shall] be subject to disciplinary action in accordance with:
13 1. For certified employees, KRS 161.120 and 161.790; or
14 2. For classified employees, KRS 161.011(7).
15 (c) A qualified school volunteer that violates paragraph (a) of this subsection
16 may[shall] be prohibited by the school district from future school volunteer
17 opportunities.
18 (4) A parent may submit written consent to authorize a designated school district
19 employee or qualified school volunteer who is not a family member to participate
20 in private electronic communication[communicate electronically] with his or her
21 child outside of the traceable communication system. The written consent:
22 (a) Shall be filed in the administrative office of the student's school;
23 (b) Shall be submitted to the administrative office prior to any private electronic
24 communication being sent from a school district employee or qualified school
25 volunteer to a student outside of the traceable communication system;
26 (c)[(b)] Shall designate each[a single,] specific school district employee or
27 qualified school volunteer[ per each consent form] that may participate in
Page 4 of 8
SB018110.100 - 175 - XXXX 1/27/2026 4:38 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 181/GA
1 private electronic communication[communicate] with the student outside of
2 the traceable communication system and shall not be transferable to any other
3 school district employee or qualified school volunteer;
4 (d)[(c)] May be revoked by the[a] parent who filed the consent at any time.
5 Upon notice of a revocation, the administrative office shall promptly notify
6 the school district and each school district employee and qualified school
7 volunteer subject to the revocation;
8 (e)[(d)] May establish terms limiting electronic communication with a student,
9 including [a term requiring that a parent be included as a direct party to all
10 electronic communications sent to the student outside of the traceable
11 communication system or ]establishing an expiration for the term of the
12 consent. Any electronic communication with the[a] student enrolled in the
13 school district outside of the traceable communication system under this
14 subsection shall comply with all terms of the written consent;[ and]
15 (f) Shall not be rejected or denied by the school or school district unless the
16 written consent fails to properly identify the applicable student, school
17 district employee, or qualified school volunteer. Upon receipt of the written
18 consent, the administrative office of the school shall deliver a copy of the
19 written consent to the school district and the designated school district
20 employee or qualified school volunteer;
21 (g) Shall not be compelled as a requirement for a student to participate in an
22 academic, athletic, or extracurricular opportunity; and
23 (h)[(e)] Shall not authorize a school district employee or qualified school
24 volunteer to engage in inappropriate or sexual electronic communication with
25 a student or be used as a basis of a defense for a school district employee or
26 qualified school volunteer that engages in inappropriate or sexual electronic
27 communication with a student or students.
